## SECTION 2: TYPOGRAPHY & GRID GEOMETRY (هندسة الخطوط)

To maintain a consistent, prestigious "Trade-Scholarly" look, use only the following typographical pairings. Headings must convey historical depth, while supporting details must convey modern clarity:

### 2.1 The Typographical Hierarchy
1.  **Book Title & Primary A+ Headers:** 
    *   *Typeface:* Classical Serifs with high stroke contrast, elegant ligatures, and structural symmetry.
    *   *Recommended Web/Print Fonts:* Garamond, Playfair Display, Sabon, Georgia, or Minion Pro.
    *   *Styling:* Bold or Medium weight, title case, generous letter-spacing (tracking) for a luxurious, spacious feel.
2.  **Subtitle, Author Name, & Supporting Details:**
    *   *Typeface:* Elegant Sans-Serif with clean, geometric proportions.
    *   *Recommended Web/Print Fonts:* Montserrat, Lato, Helvetica Neue, or Gill Sans.
    *   *Styling:* Regular or Light weight, all-caps (uppercase), and wide tracking (at least 150pt tracking) to create breathing space.

### 2.2 Grid & Alignment Rule
All elements must align to a centered, symmetric axis. The visual weight must never feel lopsided or crowded. The layout must feel structurally balanced, reflecting the meticulous legal order of *Fiqh*.

